As it turns out, some of the humans had developed the ability to levitate, but it was weak and they couldn't do it for long. So they practiced and practiced. The "Last Ones" as they called themselves, developed games and challenges that they would complete together to strengthen this magical ability.

The "Last Ones" as they called themselves, developed games and challenges that they would complete together to strengthen this magical ability.

As it turns out, some of the humans had developed the ability to levitate, but it was weak and they couldn't do it for long. So they practiced and practiced. The "Last Ones" as they called themselves, developed games and challenges that they would complete together to strengthen this magical ability.

Against all odds, the last humans tleftEon arth mhadlto earn to harness this power or drisk another attack, maybe the last. As it turns out, some of the humans had developed the ability to levitate, but it was weak and they couldn't do it for long. So they practiced and practiced. The "Last Ones" as they called themselves, developed games and challenges that they would complete together to strengthen this magical ability.

As it turns out, some of the humans had developed the ability to levitate, but it was weak and they couldn't do it for long. So they practiced and practiced. The "Last Ones" as they called themselves, developed games and challenges that they would complete together to strengthen this magical ability. 
Thirrteenyears after the alien invasion, humanity hasdbegun to understand this magic.
 Mana meant that people were not only able to levitate themselves, but other objects and creatures as well. With the regained ability of Mana, the human race felt ready once again to protect itself, should another alien attack occur. However, competition sparked between the Last Ones over who was best at it. Instead of focusing on their powers for good, about a majority of the people were competitive over who had the stronger powers. The aliens had been watching all of this unfold from afar, waiting for the right moment to attack. As it turns out, some of the humans had developed the ability to levitate, but it was weak and they couldn't do it for long. So they practiced and practiced. The "Last Ones" as they called themselves, developed games and challenges that they would complete together to strengthen this magical ability. 
Thirrteenyears after the alien invasion, humanity hasdbegun to understand this magic.
 Mana meant that people were not only able to levitate themselves, but other objects and creatures as well. With the regained ability of Mana, the human race felt ready once again to protect itself, should another alien attack occur. However, competition sparked between the Last Ones over who was best at it. Instead of focusing on their powers for good, about a majority of the people were competitive over who had the stronger powers. The aliens had been watching all of this unfold from afar, waiting for the right moment to attack. As it turns out, some of the humans had developed the ability to levitate, but it was weak and they couldn't do it for long. So they practiced and practiced. The "Last Ones" as they called themselves, developed games and challenges that they would complete together to strengthen this magical ability. 
Thirrteenyears after the alien invasion, humanity hasdbegun to understand this magic.
 Mana meant that people were not only able to levitate themselves, but other objects and creatures as well. With the regained ability of Mana, the human race felt ready once again to protect itself, should another alien attack occur. However, competition sparked between the Last Ones over who was best at it. Instead of focusing on their powers for good, about a majority of the people were competitive over who had the stronger powers. The aliens had been watching all of this unfold from afar, waiting for the right moment to attack. The Earth, once again became vulnerable to attack because people were too busy competing and fighting to care for one another or to get ready for an alien attack.
